==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Clinodiagonal
<hw>Cli`no*di*ag"o*nal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>kli`nein</grk> to incline + E. <ets>diagonal</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Crystallog.)</fld> <def>That diagonal or lateral axis in a
monoclinic crystal which makes an oblique angle with the vertical axis.
See <er>Crystallization</er>.</def> -- <def2><pos>a.</pos>
<def>Pertaining to, or the direction of, the
clinodiagonal.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Clinodome</ent>⟦br⟧
